"title": "8265: godliness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8265",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Reverence for or devotion to God, producing a practical awareness of God in every aspect of life.</p>\n<h2>Examples of godliness in the OT</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:24\">GEN 5:24</a> <em>Enoch</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:9\">GEN 6:9</a> <em>Noah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:3-1Kgs18:4\">1KI 18:3–18:4</a> <em>Obadiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:20-2Chr31:21\">2CH 31:20–31:21</a> <em>Hezekiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:1\">JOB 1:1</a> <em>Job</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of godliness in the NT</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:25\">LUK 2:25</a> <em>Simeon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a> <em>Anna</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:47\">JHN 1:47</a> <em>Nathanael</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:29\">JHN 8:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7\">HEB 5:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:5\">ACT 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:2\">ACT 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:2\">ACT 10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:7\">ACT 10:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:24\">ACT 11:24</a> <em>Barnabas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:12\">ACT 22:12</a> <em>Ananias</em></p>\n<h2>God has a special concern for the godly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:3\">PSA 4:3</a></strong> <em>“the godly” (sometimes translated “the saints”) is often used in the OT to refer to God's people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:6\">PSA 32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:31\">JHN 9:31</a></p>\n<h2>Godly living</h2>\n<h3>Godliness should be seen in the lives of believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:11\">2PE 3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:2\">1TI 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11\">1TI 6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12\">TIT 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the beginning and end of godliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a></strong> <em>The model and the power for godly living derives from the incarnate Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7\">HEB 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:3\">2PE 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>The basis for godly living is true teaching about Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:3-1Tim6:4\">1TI 6:3–6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:1\">TIT 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>Godly living demands self-discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:24-1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:24–9:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:5\">2CO 10:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:7-1Tim4:8\">1TI 4:7–4:8</a></p>\n<h3>Sorrow for sin is a sign of godliness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:10-2Cor7:11\">2CO 7:10–7:11</a></p>\n<h2>The benefits of godliness</h2>\n<h3>Its value in both this world and the next</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:8\">1TI 4:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Its present blessings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:40\">DEU 4:40</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:6\">1TI 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:10\">ISA 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:8\">TIT 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of future blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:11-Titus2:13\">TIT 2:11–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:11-2Pet3:12\">2PE 3:11–3:12</a></p>\n<h2>Godliness does not guarantee escape from suffering</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:1\">PSA 12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:2\">MIC 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:12\">2TI 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:9\">2PE 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Apparent godliness may not be genuine</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:5\">1TI 6:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:4-2Tim3:5\">2TI 3:4–3:5</a></p>",
